Durban - Police arrested four men and seized four guns and ammunition from a security company allegedly using illegal firearms in Pietermaritzburg. Colonel Thembeka Mbhele, police spokesperson, said an intelligence driven operation conducted by Pietermaritzburg Public Order Police was aimed at confiscating the illegal possession of firearms. Mbhele said the operation then led to the arrest of four men and the seizure of four firearms. “It is alleged that police received an intelligence about a security company which was hiring untrained individuals, giving them firearms with live rounds for their security guarding operations. Police pounced to a company in Jacobs and arrested the suspects. They seized two shotguns, a pistol and a revolver with a total of 16 rounds of ammunition,” she said. She said the arrested were charged with the illegal possession of firearms and ammunition and they appeared in the Durban Magistrate’s Court on Thursday. "Further investigation is continuing to determine if the security company owner or its management is continuing with the contravention of the firearms control act, if so, more arrests are imminent. We will ensure that we fight the spread of firearms in our province to protect the citizens of this country," Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Police Commissioner. Daily News